Project Report: Employee Management Application


---

1. Project Overview

The Employee Management Application is a web-based application designed to manage employee records. It allows users to perform CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on employee data. The application is built using Spring Boot for the backend, Thymeleaf for the frontend, and MySQL for the database.


---

2. Features

1. Add Employee – Users can add new employee records with details such as name, email, and department.


2. View Employee Details – Users can view detailed information about a specific employee.


3. Edit Employee – Users can update existing employee records.


4. Delete Employee – Users can remove employee records from the system.


5. Responsive Design – The application is designed to be responsive and works seamlessly on different devices.


6. Form Validation – Both frontend and backend validation ensure data integrity.




---

3. Technologies Used

Backend

Spring Boot – Framework for building the application.

Spring Data JPA – For database operations.

MySQL – Relational database for storing employee records.

RESTful APIs – For handling CRUD operations.


Frontend

Thymeleaf – Template engine for rendering HTML pages.

HTML/CSS – For structuring and styling the application.

JavaScript – For frontend validation and interactivity.

Bootstrap – For responsive design.


Tools

IntelliJ IDEA – Integrated Development Environment (IDE).

Maven – Build automation tool.

Git – Version control system.

